    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-17T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-17T22:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Kulangsu/268: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Amoy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVitty</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Amoy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-18T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 18, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 18—2 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Embassy’s telegram October 17, 9 p.m. The American and Japanese
                    landing forces will simultaneously withdraw from <pb facs="0169" n="163"
                        xml:id="pg_163"/> the International Settlement at 2 p.m., today. The request
                    for simultaneous withdrawal was made by the Japanese authorities.</p>
                <p>Sent to Peiping. Repeated to Chungking and Shanghai. Peiping repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVitty</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
